# Svelte Storybook Controls Rules

## Every component needs an args-driven Playground story defined FIRST

The first `<Story>` in each `.stories.svelte` file MUST be named `"Playground"` and must wire `defineMeta` args to the component via `{...args}` spread. This becomes the autodocs default.

### Acceptable Playground patterns

**Pattern A — auto-render (simple components):**
```svelte
<Story name="Playground" />
```
The component auto-renders with `defineMeta` args. Use for components with no snippet children.

**Pattern B — template with args spread:**
```svelte
<Story name="Playground">
  {#snippet template(args)}
    <Component {...args}>
      {#snippet children()}
        <!-- fixed demo children -->
      {/snippet}
    </Component>
  {/snippet}
</Story>
```
Use when the component requires snippet children or wrapping markup.

**Pattern C — destructured args (override specific props with local state):**
```svelte
<Story name="Playground">
  {#snippet template(args: SomeProps)}
    {@const { isOpen: _o, onDismiss: _d, ...rest } = args}
    <Component {...rest} isOpen={localState} onDismiss={handler}>
  {/snippet}
</Story>
```
Use when a prop (e.g. `isOpen`) must be driven by local `$state` rather than controls.

## Reserve asChild only for static showcase stories

`asChild` stories (matrices, fixed examples, controlled demos with buttons) are fine — they don't need args wiring. But every file MUST have at least one non-asChild Playground story that passes args.

## Stories using template() without args param must be fixed

`{#snippet template()}` renders content but ignores the Controls panel entirely. Always accept and spread args:

```svelte
// BAD
{#snippet template()}
  <Component />

// GOOD
{#snippet template(args)}
  <Component {...args} />
```

## Verification

After changes, run:
```bash
# Every component .stories.svelte should have name="Playground"
grep -L 'name="Playground"' src/components/**/*.stories.svelte

# No template() without args should remain
grep -rn '{#snippet template()}' src/
```
